text.tspan: Associations
In Tirade you can connect different Content Types. For example
* an Image to a Document
* an Image to a Gallery
* a User to a Group
* a Document to a Folder
* etc
This is how you do it.
Empty Image List
After the Image is removed, the Image list will be empty.
The pentagon pattern suggests to drop something here, preferably
an Image. Open the Sidebar and drag the relevant Image.
Edit Document
Navigate to the Document you want to assign a (new) Image to.
We assume you have added the the relevant Image to the Clipboard.
Remove Image
If the Document as already an Image assigned, you may
remove it by clicking the "minus" Button.
Drop the Image
When you hover over the (empty) Image list
of the Document, it should get activated.
Drop it to assign it.
Save the Document
The Image should now be contained in the list.
Save the Document by clicking "Submit" to
apply the changes.
